        <p>Converts the cursor to Loop mode, which lets you create a "loop" shape by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.MovieSync">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a loop shape is created. This is a useful shape for circling parts of an image that you want to emphasize. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture,Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../UI_Elements/Loop_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Loop Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
